node.text:
I love office buildings right now bc they are not in demand and there is 4 million sqft vacancy is just Orange County alone compared to 1.3 million sqft vacancy in 2008.
⠀
This creates opportunity for buying at a discount, and the biggest opportunity I see currently is repurposing the office space - especially to medical.
⠀
Medical office is still in high demand and the #1 criteria for repurposing is keeping a 6:1 parking ratio.
⠀
This has always been my investing strategy: buy low, add value, and sell high. While that never changes, the method in which you do it does, such as repurposing assets to what’s in demand today.
⠀
If you want to learn my investing blueprint on how I scaled from a $1M to $100M portfolio in only 6 years & where I'm finding great deals today, check out the new training video I released linked in my bio 🏠👉🏼🏢

node.text:
talking farsi to my fellow Iranians about this special Bugatti once belonged to Shah of Iran 😊

Today I’m delighted to have this very special bugatti here in my gallery! This is really one of a kind that belong to shah of Iran! Enjoy the video and Thank you for all your kind comments.
-
‎امروز من از داشتن این بوگاتی بسیار خاص اینجا در گالری خود خوشحالم! این واقعاً یکی از مواردی است که متعلق به شاه ایران است! از ویدیو لذت ببرید و از همه نظرات لطف شما سپاسگزارم 
.
#parchambalast #shahsbugatti #1of1

node.text:
I'm a cyclical, contrarian investor. When everyone is buying, I'm slowing down. When people are running away from an asset class, I'm running towards it bc I see tremendous opportunity in buying distressed assets that I can add value to.
⠀
With that said, there are always great deals to be found in any market, and I'm especially seeing great opportunities in the office market right now.

Currently have a couple of deals in the pipeline each of which I expect will net me multiple 7-figures.

And this process works on all deal sizes - big and small. If you want to learn my investment strategy, check out "How To Invest In Commercial Real Estate" in my bio link🎯

node.text:
I see companies moving away from high-density layouts and toward more footprint per employee.
⠀
High rises will probably be less favorable and there will be higher demand in low rise office space with indoor/outdoor flexibility.
⠀
All-in-all, companies with very high employee density and high overhead will allow more employees to work from home to reduce their footprint and look for smaller office space.
⠀
And there will be many new companies come into the market who need a strong culture with a younger workforce to fill vacancies where the larger corporations haven’t.
If you want to learn how I’m preparing for future real estate trends & identify opportunities, watch the “How To Invest In Commercial Real Estate” video linked in my bio 👊🏻

node.text:
Multi-family is great for parking your money for stable cash flow bc low vacancies and high demand but it’s not the best vehicle for growing your money quickly...
⠀
And with our current economy cycle multi-family has been hot the past 5 years and rents have almost capped out which is why I don’t focus on the asset class.
⠀
I’ve always focused on distressed, value-add properties with high capital growth potential for much larger returns.
⠀
If you want to learn more about my investing strategy, watch the How To Invest In Commercial Real Estate video linked in my bio 💥

node.text:
I love office buildings right now bc they are not in demand and there is 4 million sqft vacancy is just Orange County alone compared to 1.3 million sqft vacancy in 2008.
⠀
This creates opportunity for buying at a discount, and the biggest opportunity I see currently is repurposing the office space - especially to medical.
⠀
Medical office is still in high demand and the #1 criteria for repurposing is keeping a 6:1 parking ratio.
⠀
This has always been my investing strategy: buy low, add value, and sell high. While that never changes, the method in which you do it does, such as repurposing assets to what’s in demand today.
⠀
If you want to learn my investing blueprint on how I scaled from a $1M to $100M portfolio in only 6 years & where I'm finding great deals today, check out the new training video I released linked in my bio 🏠👉🏼🏢
